  "text": "The average contribution of onshore nuclide transport to local vertical nuclide flux was 65% [CITATION_1] . Applying the same percentage to POC flux suggests that an average of 400 mg C m 22 d 21 was locally produced while the remaining flux of 700 mg C m 22 d 21 was sourced from offshore waters. Similar findings of offshore support for coastal bivalves have been reported in marine systems [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
